  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\nIf put the app in the background in process of adding an account in Wallet, the filled seed phrase / private key field will look empty after returning in the foreground, but in fact, it will remain filled: if you enter the password again, the account will be added.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n- the field remains filled after returning to the foreground\r\nor\r\n- the field is truly cleared after returning to the foreground (like the password field) \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/67952253/189956747-e20e77fd-f922-4226-b837-256b05fb568b.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Open Wallet\r\n2. Add an account\r\n3. Enter a seed phrase\r\n4. Fill in all the fields\r\n5. Put the app in the background/switch to the app preview mode\r\n6. Re-open the app\r\n7. Enter the password\r\n8. Add an account\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly 13/09\r\n- Operating System: Android\r\n\r\n\r\n",
